---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---
<SiteLayout title="About — Simon Gelbart" current="about">
  <section class="page-heading narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>A public lab for backend architecture judgment.</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">Person first</p><h2>About the lab</h2></div>
    <div class="panel prose-panel">
      <p>I’m Simon Gelbart, a .NET-focused backend developer in France with experience building and maintaining backend systems.</p>
      <p>This site is my public engineering lab: a place where I use projects and learning material to think through backend architecture, modeling, documentation, and tooling.</p>
      <p>I care about explicit boundaries, visible trade-offs, and designs that can evolve without hiding too much in conventions or memory.</p>
      <p>Most of the work starts from the .NET ecosystem, but the questions are broader than one stack.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">Philosophy</p><h2>Experiments, not finished products.</h2></div>
    <div class="panel prose-panel">
      <p>The projects here are active experiments. Some are libraries, some are tooling ideas, and some are learning material. They are not presented as finished products. They are places where I can make ideas concrete enough to inspect, document, and improve.</p>
      <p>The best way to understand the lab is to inspect the projects, read the learning material, and follow the source.</p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/projects/">Projects</a>
        <a class="button" href="/learning-paths/">Learning paths</a>
        <a class="button" href="https://github.com/SimonGelbart" rel="noreferrer">GitHub ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-compact">
    <div class="note">The site itself is being shaped alongside the projects, so some structure may change as the lab becomes clearer.</div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
